Record Class Collaborator

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
net.tangly.erp.collaborators.domain.Collaborator
Record Components:
id - identifier is the social security number of the collaborator
oldSocialSecurityNumber - old social security number. It is an idiosyncrasy of Switzerland and optional
birthday - birthday of the collaborator
firstName - firstname as displayed on an official document
lastName - lastName as displayed on an official document
internalId - internal identifier of the collaborator used to identify in the company
address - address of the collaborator
phoneNr - work phoneNr of the collaborator as used for documents
gender - gender, only used for swissWageCard
All Implemented Interfaces:
net.tangly.core.HasId
public record Collaborator(@NotNull String id, String oldSocialSecurityNumber, @NotNull LocalDate birthday, @NotNull String firstName, @NotNull String lastName, @NotNull String internalId, @NotNull net.tangly.core.Address address, net.tangly.core.PhoneNr phoneNr, net.tangly.core.GenderCode gender) extends Record implements net.tangly.core.HasId
Defines the collaborator entity as needed from the perspective of the human resources department. The new social security number can be used as an identifier in Switzerland. The European Union has a european identifier for natural persons. The address ownership is outside this bounded domain and is owned by the CRM bounded domain.
